                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/669: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-07T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 7, 1933—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. For the Ambassador from White. Caffery reports Olaya states he has not
                    accepted the second Brazilian proposal, namely, to hold negotiations in Rio
                    before Leticia is returned to Colombia. Department is not taking matter up in
                    Lima until you can get this matter straightened out.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
